<td id="title_text"><h1><a title="Aller Undulating Ductor Roller" class="currentChild" href="Aller_Undulating_Ductor_Roller">Aller Undulating Ductor Roller</a></h1></td>



</tr></table>
</td>
</tr></table></div>



<div id="content" class="content wikipage" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<p id="l1">
A segmented <a title="Ductor Roller" href="Ductor_Roller">ductor roller</a> used in the <a title="Inking System" href="Inking_System">inking system</a> of some printing presses used in <a title="Web Offset Lithography" href="Web_Offset_Lithography">web offset lithography</a>. Each segment of the undulating roller is set off-center with respect to the other sections. Thus, some segments are picking up ink from the <a title="Fountain Roller" href="Fountain_Roller">fountain roller</a>, while others are transferring ink to the rest of the <a title="Roller Train" href="Roller_Train">roller train</a>. The Aller undulating roller accurately controls the distribution of ink laterally across the press. See <a title="Inking System: Offset Lithography" class="nonexistent" href="http://printwiki.org/Inking_System:_Offset_Lithography">Inking System: Offset Lithography</a>. 
</p>
